<i>is a laminated poplar/oak.</i>

33:54.616 --> 33:57.118
‐ Is that thing worth
$10,000?

33:57.118 --> 33:58.453
‐ I hope so.

33:58.453 --> 34:00.956
‐ Well, we're gonna find out
in our weapons test.

34:00.956 --> 34:02.249
There will be three.

34:02.249 --> 34:03.583
We'll put your blades
through a strength test,

34:03.583 --> 34:06.044
a sharpness test, and,
up first, the KEAL test.

34:06.044 --> 34:09.756
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:09.756 --> 34:12.592
‐ All right, bladesmiths,
welcome to the KEAL test.

34:12.592 --> 34:14.386
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:14.386 --> 34:16.429
I will take your weapon,
deliver some thrust and slashes

34:16.429 --> 34:19.599
on this wild boar carcass.

34:19.599 --> 34:21.268
Zane, you're up first.
You ready for this?

34:21.268 --> 34:23.228
‐ Ready as I'll ever be.

34:23.228 --> 34:25.438
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:25.438 --> 34:28.942
Ooh‐hoo‐hoo, this is the moment
I have been waiting for.

34:28.942 --> 34:30.819
<i>I have been wanting</i>
<i>to see my blade</i>

34:30.819 --> 34:32.904
<i>attack a boar</i>
<i>for the longest time,</i>

34:32.904 --> 34:34.948
and it's happening now.

34:34.948 --> 34:37.325
<i>This is gonna be</i>
<i>really awesome.</i>

34:37.325 --> 34:44.374
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:57.470 --> 35:02.350
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:02.350 --> 35:03.935
‐ All right, Zane, let's talk
about your weapon here.

35:03.935 --> 35:07.147
First up, your tip
is really made to thrust.

35:07.147 --> 35:10.066
It punctures really deep
when I'm thrusting with it,

35:10.066 --> 35:11.276
but I can move
with this weapon.

35:11.276 --> 35:12.569
You have a good balance here.

35:12.569 --> 35:14.446
The edge here is sharp.

35:14.446 --> 35:17.449
As you can see, those are
very, very deep, sharp cuts.

35:17.449 --> 35:19.409
Overall, sir, your weapon...

35:19.409 --> 35:20.493
will KEAL.

35:20.493 --> 35:22.203
‐ Thank you, Doug.

35:22.203 --> 35:23.788
‐ All right, Chris,
it's your turn.

35:23.788 --> 35:25.832
You ready?
‐ Yes, sir.

35:25.832 --> 35:28.084
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:28.084 --> 35:31.421
Zane's spontoon had a heck
of an edge on that thing.

35:31.421 --> 35:34.549
<i>I'm just hoping that mine</i>
<i>does as well or better.</i>

35:34.549 --> 35:37.302
I'm holding my breath.
[laughs]

35:37.302 --> 35:44.309
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:02.994 --> 36:06.998
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:06.998 --> 36:09.292
‐ All right, Chris, let's talk
about your weapon here.

36:09.292 --> 36:12.796
What I love about this is,
when you're thrusting,

36:12.796 --> 36:15.256
I can feel the weight in front

36:15.256 --> 36:18.551
and crunch ribs
as it's penetrating.

36:18.551 --> 36:21.054
Overall, sir, your weapon...

36:21.054 --> 36:22.013
will KEAL.

36:22.013 --> 36:23.890
‐ Thank you, sir.

36:23.890 --> 36:28.353
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:28.353 --> 36:30.897
‐ All right, gentlemen,
say hello to my little friend.

36:30.897 --> 36:33.149
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:33.149 --> 36:34.776
[laughter]

36:34.776 --> 36:37.028
To test the strength
and durability of your blades,

36:37.028 --> 36:39.322
we're gonna be firing them
out of our air cannon here

36:39.322 --> 36:40.573
into that wooden wall.

36:40.573 --> 36:42.075
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:42.075 --> 36:43.910
All right, Zane,
you're up first.

36:43.910 --> 36:45.412
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:45.412 --> 36:46.871
<i>‐ This thing is gonna launch</i>
<i>my spontoon</i>

36:46.871 --> 36:48.373
my baby,

36:48.373 --> 36:52.544
<i>at a wall of wood and try</i>
<i>its best to beat it up.</i>

36:52.544 --> 36:55.046
So my stomach is up here,

36:55.046 --> 36:57.006
my heart is on the floor
somewhere,

36:57.006 --> 36:58.591
<i>and I really don't know</i>
<i>how to feel right now.</i>

36:58.591 --> 36:59.384
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:01.386 --> 37:04.264
‐ In three, two, one.

37:04.264 --> 37:05.557
Fire.

37:05.557 --> 37:08.518
[whooshing]

37:12.647 --> 37:17.736
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:17.736 --> 37:19.446
‐ Damn.

37:19.446 --> 37:22.073
‐ All right, Zane,
nothing came apart.

37:22.073 --> 37:25.076
It still has the edge
that it started out with.

37:25.076 --> 37:26.995
All in all, good job.

37:26.995 --> 37:28.913
‐ Thank you.
‐ Nice job.

37:28.913 --> 37:30.915
‐ All right, Chris, you're up.

37:30.915 --> 37:37.130
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:37.130 --> 37:39.966
Firing in three, two, one.

37:39.966 --> 37:40.967
Fire.

37:40.967 --> 37:44.471
[whooshing]

37:44.471 --> 37:45.597
‐ Ho‐ho‐ho‐ho!
‐ Ho!

37:45.597 --> 37:47.432
‐ Wow.
‐ Good job, Chris.

37:47.432 --> 37:48.516
‐ [laughs]

37:48.516 --> 37:53.313
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:53.313 --> 37:55.315
Okay, your weapon went
right in between those boards,

37:55.315 --> 37:58.777
so it actually took all the
impact up here on these lugs.

37:58.777 --> 38:00.820
Everything's still straight,

38:00.820 --> 38:02.113
still sharp.

38:02.113 --> 38:03.782
I really like that pattern
you've got on there.

38:03.782 --> 38:05.450
Nicely done.
‐ Thank you.

38:05.450 --> 38:06.743
‐ Way to go, Chris. Nice.
‐ Thank you.

38:06.743 --> 38:07.869
Whew!

38:07.869 --> 38:12.540
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:12.540 --> 38:15.543
‐ All right, bladesmiths,
welcome to the sharpness test,

38:15.543 --> 38:17.462
the redcoat stab‐and‐slice.

38:17.462 --> 38:20.131
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:20.131 --> 38:22.634
To test the sharpness
of your edge,

38:22.634 --> 38:25.136
I will take your weapon
and slash and stab

38:25.136 --> 38:27.138
across this redcoat.

38:27.138 --> 38:29.140
Zane, you're up first.
Let's do it.

38:29.140 --> 38:36.105
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:58.378 --> 39:01.005
All right, Zane,
your edges are sharp.

39:01.005 --> 39:03.299
On the swing of that,
it does cut.

39:03.299 --> 39:04.843
But what I do find here...

39:04.843 --> 39:06.386
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:06.386 --> 39:08.555
Is a little bit of a glinting
at your tip,

39:08.555 --> 39:09.848
so it catches on my nail.

39:09.848 --> 39:13.226
So it rolled a little bit
right there at your tip.

39:13.226 --> 39:15.019
But otherwise, sir...

39:15.019 --> 39:16.020
it will cut.

39:16.020 --> 39:18.189
‐ Thank you.

39:18.189 --> 39:19.274
‐ All right, Chris, your turn.

39:19.274 --> 39:20.358
Let's do this.

39:20.358 --> 39:21.943
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:21.943 --> 39:25.572
‐ Things have actually been
really even between Zane and I.

39:25.572 --> 39:30.493
I just hope that my spontoon,
it's strong and sharp enough.

39:30.493 --> 39:31.870
<i>This is it.</i>

39:31.870 --> 39:38.918
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:57.312 --> 40:02.358
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:02.358 --> 40:06.237
‐ All right, Chris, this is
a very razor‐sharp blade.

40:06.237 --> 40:10.116
Every slash and thrust
was a deep cut.

40:10.116 --> 40:12.994
I do not see any damage
to your edge.

40:12.994 --> 40:16.247
Overall, sir, this weapon...

40:16.247 --> 40:17.624
will cut.

40:17.624 --> 40:19.584
‐ Thank you.

40:19.584 --> 40:22.086
‐ Zane, Chris, you guys
have done fantastic work

40:22.086 --> 40:23.379
on these finale weapons,

40:23.379 --> 40:25.924
but there can only be one
"Forged in Fire" champion.

40:25.924 --> 40:27.967
The judges have made
their final decision,

40:27.967 --> 40:30.762
and that "Forged in Fire"
champion is...

40:30.762 --> 40:32.764
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:32.764 --> 40:34.265
Chris.

40:34.265 --> 40:36.267
Congratulations, you are the
new "Forged in Fire" champion.

40:36.267 --> 40:38.186
‐ All right, buddy.
‐ Congratulations, man.

40:38.186 --> 40:39.646
‐ Thank you.
‐ Zane, unfortunately,

40:39.646 --> 40:42.273
your weapon took some damage
during the sharpness test

40:42.273 --> 40:44.943
which affected the efficacy
of your cuts.

40:44.943 --> 40:47.362
For that reason, I'd like
to invite you to shake my hand,

40:47.362 --> 40:48.863
shake your judges' hands,

40:48.863 --> 40:50.490
and then please leave
The Forge.

40:50.490 --> 40:51.783
Come on, my friend.

40:51.783 --> 40:53.326
‐ Meet you guys.
‐ Good job, brother.

40:53.326 --> 40:55.787
‐ I did not win,
but that's okay.

40:55.787 --> 40:56.829
‐ It's a great weapon, okay?

40:56.829 --> 40:57.997
<i>‐ I came here to prove</i>

40:57.997 --> 40:59.457
that I was able to compete

40:59.457 --> 41:00.750
<i>with some of the big dogs,</i>

41:00.750 --> 41:02.710
and I think I've made
my point.

41:02.710 --> 41:05.463
<i>I hope that I'll be able to</i>
<i>keep improving upon my craft</i>

41:05.463 --> 41:07.966
<i>and just get better</i>
<i>and better.</i>

41:07.966 --> 41:10.510
‐ Chris, you crafted
a better weapon

41:10.510 --> 41:12.303
that held up through the tests.

41:12.303 --> 41:14.472
Congratulations, you are
the "Forged in Fire" champion,

41:14.472 --> 41:16.975
and that's a title that comes
with a check for $10,000.

41:16.975 --> 41:18.142
Good job, brother.

41:18.142 --> 41:19.102
Come over here
and shake our hands.

41:19.102 --> 41:20.520
‐ Absolutely.

41:20.520 --> 41:22.146
<i>I just became</i>
<i>the "Forged in Fire" champion.</i>

41:22.146 --> 41:23.815
[laughs]
That's crazy.

41:23.815 --> 41:26.484
<i>I'm, like, turning inside out</i>
<i>right now.</i>

41:26.484 --> 41:27.860
I got the bragging rights, man.

41:27.860 --> 41:30.321
<i>I can just keep moving ahead,</i>

41:30.321 --> 41:31.656
keep doing what I'm doing.

41:31.656 --> 41:38.663
<i>♪ ♪</i>
